node.text:
BROTHERHOOD
I made this plaque as a reminder for @kevin.p.owens service on our Sniper Detachment in WAR. A brotherhood isn’t defined by material mementos or tangible things, but it’s a tradition to give teammates a reminder of their impact. 
-
The unspoken promise is made to each other, to the brotherhood and regiment every single night in combat… that oath doesn’t depart with leaving service. 
-
We will defend the Constitution of the United States against all enemies, foreign and domestic. No rank, no insignia, no designation needed. 
-
I’m not worried… I’m just living that PREPPED life, watching it all unfold reflecting on some amazing years. 
-
#brotherhood #war #sniper #crf #cif

node.text:
We The Crazy
You were born into flinging poop and eating dirt. Somewhere along the line you got civilized, I’m all about that life. What’s an evolving life without some semblance of order.
-
You’re all crazy. You, me, We the Crazies.
-
Some of you’re saying right now… “What’s this dude talking about? I’m not crazy.” You’re the craziest lol. Just because you mask it well doesn’t mean you ain’t. You’re just better at hiding it, oh man but when it comes out, it’s like astronaut drive across the country in a diaper crazy. 
-
It’s not the crazies that concern me. It’s those actors pretending to be perfect. The influencers, the politicians, “thought leaders” whatever the f*uck that means.
-
I want inconsistency, I want trauma, I want the lows and heavy burdens… for Gods sake what beautiful comparisons, contrast and perspectives can you manifest from a perfect existence.
-
Give me grounded, salt of the earth, with a little sprinkle of BAT SHIT and you’ll find me in my happy place.
-
On a scale of 1-10, 10 being bat shit where would you rank yourself? Come on Karen’s, where you at?

node.text:
UTOPIA
We add, we refine, we evolve… or do we?
-
The evolution of societal architecture favors utopia over reality. We stack people on top of each other like neat and efficient lego blocks-supposedly optimized for evolutionary success.
-
It briefs well, but never executed the same.
-
São Paulo, Brazil (3rd Pic) is the largest city in Latin America, nearly a Third live in slum like conditions that feel like a war zone.
-
What’s the future for America?
-
Politicians hold power in heavy populated city centers because they drive votes from dependence on their policies. While the less populated areas operate more decentralized with less dependence. 
-
New York has become the first state in the US to declare an emergency to tackle increasing levels of gun violence, directing extra funds for programmes aimed at preventing shootings.
"More people are now dying from gun violence and crime than Covid," state governor Andrew Cuomo said. *BBC
-
The WILD CARD in your Utopia is people.
-
“Men come and go, cities rise and fall, whole civilizations appear and disappear-the earth remains, slightly modified. The earth remains, and the heartbreaking beauty where there are no hearts to break....I sometimes choose to think, no doubt perversely, that man is a dream, thought an illusion, and only rock is real. Rock and sun.” Edward Abbey
-
What’s our solution? Leave me feedback in comments.

MUSHROOMS
I love foraging for mushrooms.
-
I found a trove of King Boletus (boletus edulis) near the aspen/birch tree line at 9000ft. It’s my first time finding one and one of my favorites. Sautéed with butter and olive oil, with a pinch of Himalayan salt. I’m Korean so it paired nice with rice, and kimchi, as does everything. Topped of with a Pliny the Elder…
-
Find hobbies outside of the whirlwind that is social. Get your ass outside and forage, fish, hunt, hike… YOLO. Your life is to short to be cooped up in your hen house.
#mushrooms #forage #getoutside

node.text:
ALL SECURE
Had an amazing event with @tomsatterly and @jensatterly from @allsecurefoundation
-
When I met Tom he was a CSM from the Unit, and I was a newly promoted CIF TM Sgt., leaving USASOC to stand a CIF up. Hearing Tom’s origin story made me miss the military and brought back a flood of memories. 
-
The significance of Tom’s wars wasn’t just on the streets of Mogadishu, or the fight in the GWOT, but the fight that was nearly lost in transitioning out of it all. Tom’s honesty, Jens empathy and understanding is a story we all need to read and understand, as it applies to our lives.
-
It’s the classic human story of adversity.
-
Human finds purpose, loses said purpose and struggles to pick up the pieces.
-
I encourage you to read “All Secure”, a book vetted through the UNIT-Intel section on Tom’s life and struggle. And get involved with organizations like @allsecurefoundation that are helping WARRIORS as they serve, as they fight-not just in war, but in a battle within.
-
Thanks Tom and Jen for sharing your stories with us.
-
This weeks Mike Force podcast is PT1 with Jen and Tom. 
-
#war #allsecure #usasoc #warriors
